fields.description:
The Customs Institute of the State Customs Committee of the Republic of Uzbekistan (established in 2003) is a higher military educational institution that trains highly qualified officers for customs authorities.

Education at the Institute is conducted on a full-time basis under state grants, with cadets provided with free uniforms, meals, and stipends.

Key information about the Institute:

Status: Higher military educational institution;
Location: Tashkent, Qatortol Street;
Field of study: Primarily BachelorŌĆÖs degree programs in ŌĆ£Customs AffairsŌĆØ;
Admission process: Includes preliminary selection (documents review, medical examination, physical fitness assessment) and specialized entrance examinations;
Benefits: Cadets receive free uniforms, meals, and financial support during their studies;
Activities: The academic process emphasizes international customs standards, analytical thinking, and the acquisition of modern knowledge.

